The deputy governor confirmed that his vehicle was involved in a head-on-collision with the boda-boda.At the time of the accident, the deputy governor had two of his aides in the vehicle.  Kisii Deputy Governor Joash Maangi’s official vehicle was on Wednesday evening torched by an angry mob after it hit and killed a boda-boda rider and his passenger in Ololulung’a, Narok County. 

The motorcyclist, Mr John Saanyo and his 8-year-old son, died on the spot after being knocked down by the governor's vehicle. 



